Episodes.Title: Big Head Bites It
Episodes.Plot: Master hunter Junior Edwards and his older son, Willie, make special weapons and specially designed hooks; Trapper Joe L'enfant and his stepson Tommy, hit the marshlands, where careless Tommy puts his life at risk.

Episodes.Title: Houdini's Last Escape
Episodes.Plot: Troy enters cypress groves in search of a monster gator that's escaped his traps for years; Junior enters a different kind of foreign territory as he reluctantly hosts the ultimate greenhorn, an Italian leather buyer

Episodes.Title: Troy's Gamble
Episodes.Plot: Troy desperately needs to find a new honey hole; Joe and Tommy contend with their own greenhorn; the Kliebard family shows they don't need the aid of computers or a factory.

Episodes.Title: Cannibal Gator
Episodes.Plot: Joe and Tommy come up against the notorious cannibal gator they call, Godzilla; Mike tries to pass down his vast swamp knowledge to his son T-Mike; Troy's lines are empty, putting his season in jeopardy.

Episodes.Title: Forces of Nature
Episodes.Plot: A cold spell is coming that could end the season early, putting the gator hunters in a race against time to beat the storm.

Episodes.Title: Family Feuds
Episodes.Plot: Halfway through the alligator season stress is taking a toll on families throughout the swamp; Joe and Tommy fight, frustrating Troy; Howard McCrea tracks a deadly gator.

Episodes.Title: Swamp Wars
Episodes.Plot: As the the end of gator season approaches, Tommy and Joe have a poacher after their catch; Junior and Willie try different ways to earn cash.

Episodes.Title: Gator Voodoo
Episodes.Plot: With a week left in the season, the gators have mysteriously stopped biting; swampers fight back with their own tried-and-true tactics as well as some new territories.

Episodes.Title: Final Countdown
Episodes.Plot: It's the final two days of alligator season. There are still a lot of gators to catch, not the least of which is the big daddy of all cannibal gators, the one known as the "Loch Ness Monster." Troy faces his ultimate nemesis, as other swampers race to end the season.

Episodes.Title: The Last Battle
Episodes.Plot: With just a few days left in the season, the pressure's intensifying. Can the swampers "tag out" in time?
